95% CI for $\mu_{caff} - \mu_{ctrl}$:

::::: columns
::: {.column width="53%"}
$$
\begin{aligned}
\overline{x}_{\text{caff}} - \overline{x}_{\text{ctrl}} & \pm t^* \cdot \sqrt{\frac{s_{\text{caff}}^2}{n_{\text{caff}}}+\frac{s_{\text{ctrl}}^2}{n_{\text{ctrl}}}} \\
248.114 - 244.514 & \pm 2.032 \cdot \sqrt{\frac{2.621^2}{35}+\frac{2.318^2}{35}} \\
3.6 & \pm 2.032 \cdot \sqrt{0.196 + 0.154} \\
(2.398, & 4.802) 
\end{aligned}
$$
:::

::: {.column width="47%"}
Used $t^*$ = `qt(0.975, df=34)` = 2.032

 

**Conclusion:**\
We are 95% confident that the difference in (population) mean finger taps/min between the caffeine and control groups is between 2.398 mg/dL and 4.802 mg/dL.
